                  <persName id="t18311201-268-person2030">
                  JAMES 
                  GRIFFIN
               <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2030" type="surname" value="GRIFFIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2030" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2030" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I work in the <placeName id="t18311201-268-crimeloc1426">London-docks</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-268-crimeloc1426" type="placeName" value="London-docks"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-268-crimeloc1426" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-268-off1423 t18311201-268-crimeloc1426"></join>. On the 25th of October, about half-past eight o'clock, I saw the prisoner go into the spirit shed; he found the spelter, took some of it, and put it under his trousers; he then went to a pile of wood - I watched him for about ten minutes; Mr. Scott, the warehouse-keeper, came by, and I told him - I then went and asked him what he had done with the spelter - he denied having had any; I told Mr. Scott where I had seen him go; he went and found this spelter there - here are 16 lbs. of it: I have seen the prisoner about the docks, but I do not know that he worked there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-268-person2031">
                  JOHN 
                  BARNES
               <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2031" type="surname" value="BARNES"></interp>
