                     <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2031" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I found the spelter behind the pile of wood in the yard.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-268-person2032">
                  DANIEL 
                  CLEMENTS
               <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2032" type="surname" value="CLEMENTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2032" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-268-person2032" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the service of the Dock Company. On the morning of the 25th of October, a little before nine o'clock, the prisoner was brought up to the watch-house, with this piece of spelter - he never worked there; the shed where the spelter was was open, and he might make a passage through there, but he had no right there; I have no doubt of this being the property of the London Dock Company.</p>
